test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e8f68a2e480>([43])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e8f68a2e480> = [[1, 43], [1, 43, 1], [43], [43, 1], [1, 43], [1, 43, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e8f68a2e480>([1, 43])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e8f68a2e480> = [[1, 43], [1, 43, 1], [43], [43, 1], [1, 43], [1, 43, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e8f68a2e480>([43, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7e8f68a2e480> = [[1, 43], [1, 43, 1], [43], [43, 1], [1, 43], [1, 43, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:

 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
